[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of cases of COVID-19 worldwide is now 722 088 with 81 470 (11.3%) cases reported by China. There are now a total of 640 618 confirmed cases of COVID-19 reported from 203 countries/locations outside mainland China, representing an increase of 58 317 cases when compared with the data on 28 Mar 2020, with the USA accounting for 18 320 (31.4%), Italy for 5217 (8.9%), Spain for 6875 (11.8%) and Germany for 4740 (8.1%) of the newly confirmed cases. The total number of confirmed cases reported from outside China now represents 88.7% of the total number of reported cases. The epicenter has shifted outside of China to Western Europe and the USA. The USA now represents 19.7% of the global cases of COVID-19. The USA and Italy have surpassed China in total number of cases. A global total of 33 976 deaths have been reported, 30 672 (90.3%) outside mainland China.

It is now clear that while China has the largest population in the world, and was the original location where the COVID-19 outbreak started, it has markedly reduced transmission to a manageable level, now monitoring all arrivals in the country from outside. South Korea has slowly decreased daily new case counts hovering around 100 in recent days. The USA is now number one outside of China for numbers of confirmed cases of COVID-19 and Italy is number 2. Iran has slowed down in growth rate and Spain has been accelerating. To get an understanding of how rapidly things increase, look at Turkey. The 1st confirmed case was reported on 11 Mar 2020 and in 18 days the country has confirmed 9217 cases. - Mod.MPP]

