[The Northern Mariana Islands are a Commonwealth of the USA and are located in the Western Pacific. Travel histories for the 2 confirmed cases have one traveling to Guam, but the other just traveled to other islands (Saipan and Tinian) in the Northern Marian Islands group, suggesting there may already have been undetected transmission of the SARS-CoV-2 in the island group. A media report outlined the challenges faced by these USA territories (specifically the Northern Mariana Islands and American Samoa) where they do not have certified laboratories to permit them to test for the SARS-CoV-2, so specimens are sent to other locations including CDC, but not all suspected cases meet the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention's criteria for testing. The challenges of being small island overseas territories. (http://www.mvariety.com/regional-news/2787-american-samoa-s-coronavirus-conundrum-no-way-to-test) - Mod.MPP

